,941-15,954; Grenfell, T.C., Warren, S.G., Mullen, P.C., Reflection of solar radiation by the Antarctic snow surface at ultraviolet, visible, and near-infrared wavelengths (1994) J. Geophys. Res., 99, pp. 18,669-18,684; Grenfell, T.C., Light, B., Sturm, M., Spatial distribution and radiative effects of soot in the snow and sea ice during the SHEBA experiment (2002) J. Geophys. Res., 107 (C10), p. 8032. , doi:10.1029/2000JC000414; Gribbon, P.W.F., Cryoconite holes on Sermikavsak, West Greenland (1979) J. Glaciol., 22, pp. 177-181; Hansen, J., Nazarenko, L., Soot climate forcing via snow and ice albedos (2003) Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. U. S. A., 101 (2), pp. 423-428. , doi:10.1073/pnas.2237157100; Higuchi, K., Nagoshi, A., Effect of particulate matter in surface snow layers on the albedo of perennial snow patches (1977) IAHS AISH Publ., 118, pp. 95-97; Jacobson, M.Z., Development and application of a new air pollution modeling system. II: Aerosol module structure and design (1997) Atmos. Environ., 31, pp. 131-144; Jacobson, M.Z., Development and application of a new air pollution modeling system, III: Aerosol-phase simulations (1997) Atmos. Environ., 31, pp. 587-608; Jacobson, M.Z., (1999) Fundamentals of Atmospheric Modeling, , Cambridge Univ. Press, New York; Jacobson, M.Z., A physically-based treatment of elemental carbon optics: Implications for global direct forcing of aerosols (2000) Geophys. Res. Lett., 27, pp. 217-220; Jacobson, M.Z., Strong radiative heating due to the mixing state of black carbon in atmospheric aerosols (2001) Nature, 409, pp. 695-697; Jacobson, M.Z., GATOR-GCMM: A global- Through urban-scale air pollution and weather forecast model: 1. Model design and treatment of subgrid soil, vegetation, roads, rooftops, water, sea ice, and snow (2001) J. Geophys. Res., 106, pp. 5385-5402; Jacobson, M.Z., GATOR-GCMM: 2, A study of daytime and nighttime ozone layers aloft, ozone in national parks, and weather during the SARMAP field campaign (2001) J. Geophy